The paper deals with the complexity of satisfiability of $k$-CNF formulas, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the construction of graph-instances and linear systems, which are common topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the probability of success of algorithms, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and randomized algorithms (cs.DS).
